  (text "UNO Q SUPER CARRIER — Rev 0.1 — BLOCK DIAGRAM\n\nSignal flow (IEEE 315: left→right, power top→bottom):\n\n  J_VIN (7-24V) ──> [POWER] ──> +5V (TPS54331 buck), +3V3 (AMS1117)\n  J_HUB (5V) ──> [POWER] ──> +5V_HUB75 (direct to panel)\n  B1/B2 (JMISC/JMEDIA) ──> [UNO Q MOUNTING] ──> SPI/I2C/MIPI/GPIO\n  [UNO Q MOUNTING] ──> SPI ──> [ESP32-S3] + [ESP32-C6]\n  [ESP32-S3] ──> HUB75 GPIO ──> [HUB75 DRIVER] ──> panel IDC\n  [ESP32-S3] ──> I2S ──> [AUDIO CODEC] ──> line-out / mic-in\n  [ESP32-S3] ──> UART ──> [ESP32-C6] (direct, independent of UNO Q)\n  [UNO Q MOUNTING] ──> MIPI DSI ──> [DISPLAY CHAIN]\n    [DISPLAY CHAIN]: CBTL04GP054 switch ──> LT8618SX ──> J_HDMI (micro-HDMI Type D)\n                                        └──> J_DSI (22-pin FPC, RPi5 display)\n  [UNO Q MOUNTING] ──> MIPI CSI ──> [RPi5 INTERFACE] ──> J_CSI0/J_CSI1 (22-pin FPC)\n  [UNO Q MOUNTING] ──> MPU GPIO 1.8V ──> [LEVEL SHIFTERS] ──> 3.3V\n  [LEVEL SHIFTERS] ──> [RPi5 INTERFACE] ──> J_GPIO40 (40-pin)\n  [LEVEL SHIFTERS] ──> DSI_SW_SEL ──> [DISPLAY CHAIN]\n  [UNO Q MOUNTING] ──> I2C ──> [EXPANSION] ──> Qwiic x2, Grove x5\n\nSub-sheets (10 total):\n  sheets/power.kicad_sch            TPS54331 buck, AMS1117, FB1, indicators\n  sheets/uno_q_mounting.kicad_sch   B1 JMISC + B2 JMEDIA (Samtec FTSH-130-01)\n  ../shield/sheets/esp32s3.kicad_sch  ESP32-S3-WROOM-1-N16R8 (shared with shield)\n  sheets/esp32c6_radio.kicad_sch    ESP32-C6-MINI-1, antenna select, USB-C debug\n  ../shield/sheets/hub75_driver.kicad_sch  74HCT245 x2, HUB75 IDC (shared)\n  ../shield/sheets/audio_codec.kicad_sch   ES8388, AGND star, line-out/mic (shared)\n  sheets/display_chain.kicad_sch    CBTL04GP054 + LT8618SX + micro-HDMI-D + DSI FPC\n  sheets/rpi5_interface.kicad_sch   40-pin GPIO, 24C32 EEPROM, CSI0/CSI1 FPC\n  sheets/level_shift.kicad_sch      TXS0108E x2 (1.8V→3.3V MPU GPIO)\n  sheets/expansion.kicad_sch        Qwiic x2, Grove x5, PSSI, I2C4, OpAmp breakout\n\nKey design decisions:\n  Micro-HDMI Type D (Molex 47151-2001) — RPi5 compatible cable\n  C6 antenna: R_ANT_PCB (0Ω populated) / R_ANT_EXT (0Ω DNP) + U.FL J_ANT\n  C6 module edge overhang required — see esp32c6_radio.kicad_sch\n  No PCIe: QRB2210 has no PCIe root complex — documented limitation"
    (at 20 260 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top)))
)
